Quantitative Trader - Cryptocurrency

About our Client and the Role

Our client is a global proprietary trading firm focused on digital asset liquidity and cryptocurrency market making. The firm is looking to hire experienced quantitative traders with either established high frequency crypto strategies or those with a strong interest in trading crypto. You’ll work on building systematic trading strategies focusing on liquidity provisioning in mainstream coins and other digital assets.

Responsibilities
• Research, develop, trade, and manage high frequency or market making strategies in cryptocurrencies and other digital assets;
• Use quantitative research techniques to conduct alpha research, back testing, implementation, and manage strategy risk and exposure;
• Collaborate with teams across an organization, such as risk management, data groups, and leadership teams/executives;

Requirements
• A portable cryptocurrency trading strategy, for which you must own the IP and a verifiable track record, with at least 2 years of live trading history;
• A Sharpe Ratio of 3.0+ and strong, consistent returns;
• Effective risk management capabilities;
• Ability to communicate clearly and distill information with leadership about trading performance;
• Bachelors, Masters, or PhD degree in a quantitative field such as computer science, mathematics, statistics, physics, or other similar technical disciplines;
• Experience with C++, C, Java, or other object oriented programming language;

In accordance with New York City’s Pay Transparency Law, the base salary range for this role is $125,000 to $250,000 and is specific to New York City. Base salary does not include other forms of compensation or benefits such as a discretionary bonus, health, dental, and other wellness plans and 401(k) contributions. Discretionary bonuses can be a significant portion of total compensation. Actual compensation for successful candidates will be carefully determined based on a number of factors, including their skills, qualifications and experience.

About Point Three Group

Point Three Group is helping redefine the future of computational finance. Our goal is to fuel research progress, foster innovation, and shape the financial landscape by connecting the brightest minds in research, trading, and engineering with leading investment firms. We bring unparalleled industry experience, honed through years of internal recruiting at some of the biggest and most successful companies in finance and tech. Our insider knowledge of the qualities and skills that make candidates exceptional gives us a deeper edge in understanding our clients’ needs and recruiting talent that exceeds expectations.

At Point Three, we don’t just find talent; we discover the future of finance.

We are seeking a seasoned Quantitative Trading Strategist to drive the development of cutting-edge trading and risk infrastructure for our protocol vaults. This key role will focus on crafting systematic trading strategies to provide liquidity and generate profit, leveraging data analysis and innovative problem-solving techniques to optimize execution.

The ideal candidate will have a strong background in mathematical modeling, programming languages like Python or C++, and financial derivatives markets. A solid understanding of probability theory, statistics, and numerical methods is essential. Experience with back-testing, simulation, and statistical analysis is also required.

The successful candidate will be responsible for:
• Building and refining trading strategies to meet business objectives;
• Leveraging data-driven insights to enhance decision-making and scale existing strategies;
• Applying creative problem-solving techniques to optimize execution and minimize risks.

This is an exciting opportunity for a highly skilled quantitative professional to join our team and contribute to shaping the future of financial services. We offer a collaborative environment, comprehensive training, and opportunities for career growth and development.

You will be part of a diverse team that values innovation, teamwork, and open communication. If you are passionate about quantitative finance and eager to take your skills to the next level, we encourage you to apply.
Key Responsibilities:Strategy Development:
• Develop systematic trading strategies to provide liquidity and generate profit;
• Analyze market trends and sentiment to inform strategy decisions;
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate trading strategies into broader business initiatives.
Data-Driven Optimization:
• Leverage data analytics tools to analyze trading metrics and identify areas for improvement;
• Implement data-driven optimization techniques to enhance strategy performance;
• Communicate insights and recommendations to stakeholders to drive informed decision-making.
Creative Problem Solving:
• Apply innovative problem-solving techniques to optimize trading execution and minimize risks;
• Design and implement complex systems to manage trading workflows and automate processes;
• Collaborate with colleagues to share knowledge and best practices in quantitative finance.

In addition to your technical expertise, you will need to possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills to effectively collaborate with colleagues and communicate complex ideas to non-technical stakeholders. If you are a motivated and results-driven individual with a passion for quantitative finance, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity.

