AECO Pacific Services is hiring an Energy Markets Analyst for their Electricity Portfolio in Singapore. The role involves analyzing customer energy usage, assisting in tenders, and office administration. Candidates should have a degree in Engineering, Math, or Finance, and possess strong analytical and communication skills. The position offers growth opportunities in a team focused on renewable energy solutions. Salary is SGD 60K–SGD 80K annually.
Position: Energy Markets Analyst (Electricity Portfolio)
About You

Are you looking for a challenging role where you can grow personally and be an integral part of a dynamic, proactive, and dedicated team? Are you a focused individual who works best with defined tasks in a well-defined process and are results-driven? Are you seeking a professional career with prospects for advancement in a growing team? If so, this opportunity might be right for you!
The

Opportunity

We are seeking a highly motivated individual with a degree in Engineering, Math, or Finance to join our Energy Markets & Energy Services team immediately. You will be part of a distributed team with members from various countries.
The Role

ESEM supports the sales team, account management, energy market analysis, and settlements by collating and preparing data to submit energy tender requests to retailer partners (Energy Companies).

You will ensure daily system requirements meet business needs and develop improvements to maintain our technological edge.
Key Responsibilities
• Analyze customer energy usage:
• Assist in producing tenders and product proposals;
• Develop and use spreadsheet models;
• Model customer energy usage as needed.
• Office administration:
• Assist in delivering services to customers;
• Perform general office duties;
• Adhere to legal, statutory, and company policies;
• Create and maintain ISO documentation;
• Follow corporate ethics: "Smart, Rigorous, and Trustworthy";
• Work within quality and safety guidelines;
• Complete tasks efficiently, cost-effectively, and auditable.
Qualifications and Experience
• Degree in Engineering, Math, or equivalent;
• Professional registration or membership preferred;
• Proficiency in Microsoft Office, especially Excel;
• Strong literacy and numeracy skills;
• Analytical and problem-solving skills;
• Attention to detail and accuracy;
• Ability to work effectively in a team;
• Time management skills;
• Flexibility to adapt to changing demands;
• Excellent communication skills;
• Experience analyzing energy usage is a plus.About Us

AECO Energy operates in renewable and deregulated electricity markets across Australia, Singapore, and the Philippines, expanding in Asia with renewable energy solutions. Founded in 2002 and headquartered in Singapore, AECO is an innovative energy technology, solutions, and trading company.
